  "text": "The Kubernetes API server authentication chain is constructed in `pkg/kubeapiserver/authenticator/config.go`. The `Config.New()` function (lines 107-248) orchestrates the complete authentication flow. It builds an authenticator chain that tries multiple authentication mechanisms in sequence until one succeeds.\n\n**Authenticator Chain Construction**: The `Config.New()` function in `pkg/kubeapiserver/authenticator/config.go` is the main entry point. It constructs a union of different authenticators that are tried in order: (1) request header authenticators (front-proxy), (2) X509/client certificate authenticators, and (3) bearer token authenticators.\n\n**Bearer Token Authenticator**: Implemented in `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/authentication/request/bearertoken/bearertoken.go`. The `Authenticator` struct and `New()` function (line 36) extract and validate bearer tokens from the Authorization header (line 42-76). This authenticator delegates to token-level authenticators to verify the token content.\n\n**Client Certificate Authenticator**: Implemented in `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/authentication/request/x509/x509.go`. The `Authenticator` struct and `NewDynamic()` function (line 133) verify client certificates from TLS connections. The `AuthenticateRequest()` method (line 138) extracts peer certificates from the TLS connection, verifies them against trusted CAs, and converts them to user information using a `UserConversion` interface.\n\n**Service Account Token Authenticator**: Implemented in `pkg/serviceaccount/jwt.go`. The `JWTTokenAuthenticator()` function (line 227) creates a JWT token authenticator that validates service account tokens. It's used in `pkg/kubeapiserver/authenticator/config.go` at lines 142 and 149, where it's called via `newLegacyServiceAccountAuthenticator()` and `newServiceAccountAuthenticator()`. The authenticator verifies JWT signatures and validates token claims against service accounts in the cluster.\n\n**Anonymous Authenticator**: Implemented in `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/authentication/request/anonymous/anonymous.go`. The `NewAuthenticator()` function (line 55) creates an authenticator that grants all unauthenticated requests the \"system:anonymous\" user and \"system:unauthenticated\" group. This is used as a fallback in `pkg/kubeapiserver/authenticator/config.go` (lines 232-245) when anonymous auth is enabled.\n\n**Request Header Authenticator**: Implemented in `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/authentication/request/headerrequest/requestheader.go`. The `NewDynamicVerifyOptionsSecure()` function (line 115) creates an authenticator for front-proxy authentication that verifies proxy client certificates and extracts user identity from headers.\n\n**Union Authenticators**: Two union implementations create chains: `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/authentication/request/union/union.go` chains multiple request authenticators (line 36), and `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/authentication/token/union/union.go` chains multiple token authenticators (line 36). Both support failing on first error via `NewFailOnError()` or continuing to the next authenticator on failure."
